<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>For My Pookie 💌</title>
  <style>
    body {
      background: linear-gradient(to right, #ffe6f0, #e6f7ff);
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 50px;
      color: #333;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 40px;
      color: #ff4d6d;
    }

    .card {
      background: white;
      padding: 20px;
      margin: auto;
      width: 70%;
      border-radius: 20px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
    }

    p {
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .heart {
      font-size: 30px;
      color: red;
    }

    button {
      background: #ff4d6d;
      color: white;
      border: none;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      font-size: 16px;
      border-radius: 10px;
      cursor: pointer;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    button:hover {
      background: #ff1a4d;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <h1>For My Pookie 💌</h1>

  <div class="card">
    <p class="heart">💖</p>
    <p>
      Even if miles are between us,<br>
      my heart still finds its way to you.<br><br>

      I made this little space just to remind you:<br>
      You are my favorite place in the world. 🌷
    </p>

    <button onclick="alert('I miss you more than words can say 💕')">
      Click me
    </button>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
